scopecontent.p:
						Description: Written in Latin on parchment
						in a late Carolingian script with some Praegothica features (uncial “D” and
						enclosed “G”). Red capitals and rubrication, and chants with diastematic
						neumes. Including feasts of saints Vitus, Lawrence, Hermes, Augustine, John
						the Baptist, Martial, Ludmila, and Benedict. 
Provenance: Lost description by Margot Fassler, May 1979.
						Formerly f.25 (1-4). 
ID Number:
						CornellMedMS_024_009.jpg (1a); CornellMedMS_024_010.jpg (1b);
						CornellMedMS_024_006.jpg (2a); CornellMedMS_024_005.jpg (2b);
						CornellMedMS_024_007.jpg (3a); CornellMedMS_024_008.jpg (3b);
						CornellMedMS_024_001.jpg (4a); CornellMedMS_024_002.jpg (4b);
						CornellMedMS_024_003.jpg (4c); CornellMedMS_024_004.jpg (4d).

